hysical and mental functioning. Its association with Acute Stress Disorder emphasizes the disorder's impact on both emotional and physical well-being. [Data: Entities (2412), Relationships (2804)]\n\n## Psychomotor Inhibition as a symptom\n\n**Psychomotor Inhibition** is another symptom of Acute Stress Disorder, characterized by slowed physical and mental activity, sometimes leading to stupor or muteness. This symptom reflects the disorder's ability to induce severe psychological and physical inhibition, further complicating treatment and recovery. Its relationship with Acute Stress Disorder highlights the disorder's capacity to manifest in ways that significantly impair daily functioning. [Data: Entities (2413), Relationships (2805)]"], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}